%N A328081 Irregular triangle read by rows: T(n,k), n >= 0, k >= 1, =  number of cells of area k/t^2 in generation n of Jim Conant's iterative dissection of a square, where t = 2^ceiling(n/2).
%C A328081 This tiling is described in A328078.  At generation n, the construction requires that each edge of the square be divided into t = 2^ceiling(n/2) segments. Then 1/t^2 is the area of the smallest possible region at generation n.
%C A328081 Sum_k T(n,k) = A328078(n), Sum_k k*T(n,k) = 4^ceiling(n/2).
